Low Ligt Image Enhancement with galamo

Welcome to the tutorial on using galamo, a Python package designed for comprehensive galaxy analysis.

Abstract: In this tutorial, we'll explore the psr module that helps in enhancing the low light images of lunar surfaces.

This modules is under testing and need imrpovements and was made as a part of ISRO Space Hackathon 2024.

Keywords: psr, image enhancement, galamo

Author: Jashanpreet Singh Dingra

Lets get started!

!pip install galamo

In[1]:
from galamo import psr
psr.enhance("moon-example1.jpg", show=True)

In[3]:
from galamo import psr

# Just enhance and show
psr.enhance("moon-example2.jpg", show=True)

# Increase gamma correction (brighter) and sharpening
psr.enhance("moon-example2.jpg", gamma=1.5, sharp=0.7, show=True)

# Lower gamma (darker) with less sharpening
psr.enhance("moon-example2.jpg", gamma=0.8, sharp=0.3, show=True)

# Save the enhanced image as PNG
psr.enhance("moon-example2.jpg", gamma=1.3, sharp=0.6, save_as="enhanced.png")

# Save directly as PDF
psr.enhance("moon-example2.jpg", gamma=1.3, sharp=0.6, save_as="enhanced.pdf")
